Section section_02 (Chars 7814–11759):
Section Summary: Debby, a young girl, is scolded by her mistress, Mrs. Lane, for not praying and seeking forgiveness for her sins. Debby refuses to obey Mrs. Lane's orders, including one to stop seeing her friend Jack Martin, and is subsequently physically punished. After being sent to her room, Debby reflects on her life and thinks about her mother and father, wondering what her father is doing and if he is still alive. She also thinks about the rumors of battles at Lexington and Bunker Hill, and how she would have liked to fight against the King if she were a boy. As the evening approaches, Debby awaits Mrs. Lane's return, knowing she will face further punishment if she doesn't show repentance.
